// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Template Editor 3.80 (2019) - User defined attributes (=UDA)
// =====================================================
// 
// This file contains attributes which are defined in the 'objects.inp'.
// 
// Notes:
// - Please use the predefined folder 'USERDEFINED' for the each attributes in this file.
// - Installation of Tekla Structures overwrites always this file.
//
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// This file contains the defined attributes and their default values for a value field.
// 
// The structure of 'contentattributes_USERDEFINED.lst' is the following. The file is divided
// into two sections, which are sperated with the line [BINDINGS]. The first section defines
// all attributes and the default settings for those attributes. The 2nd section assigns
// the attributes to contenttypes. Attributes are presented to the user in the order they
// appear in the definition list for contenttypes.
//
// A special case of a component type is ALL, which defines that the attributes defined in 
// the following lines are available to all types of components. Other special types are
// HEADER, PAGEHEADER, PAGEFOOTER and FOOTER.
// 
// You can use a virtual node to group certain attributes under a common subnode. A virtual
// node is defined inside []. This doesn't affect the name of the actual attribute - text
// between [] is removed when the attribute name is inserted into a template definition.
//
// You can add comment text for the user attributes by defining it between "-characters after
// the attribute name.
// 
// The attribute definition line is divided into nine different columns. The star character
// '*' means that the default value should be used or that this property doesn't apply to
// this type of valuefield.
// 
// The attribute dividing to the different versions can be done by using extension #1...N
// in attribute name.
//
// The columns are
// 
// 1. Attribute name (maximum of 63 characters. Use only letters, numbers, dots and underlines)
// 2. Data type (FLOAT, CHARACTER, INTEGER)
// 3. Value field justification (LEFT, CENTER, RIGHT)
// 4. Is the field cacheable (TRUE or FALSE, TRUE is default)
// 5. Value field length (characters)
// 6. The number of decimals (present only if data type is FLOAT, and no precision defined)
// 7. The unit type
// 8. The unit
// 9. The precision
// 										
// Name				Datatype	Justify Cacheable	Length	Decimals 	Unit type 	Unit 		Precision
// XXXX				CHARACTER	RIGHT	TRUE		8		2 			Length		ft-frac		1/8
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

// TAB_ISSO
isso_element_constr	CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15
isso_naimen_1		CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15
isso_naimen_2	    CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15
isso_seria          CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15
isso_constr		    CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15
isso_massa	        CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15
isso_beton        	CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15
isso_polz_pole	    CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15
isso_gr_object      CHARACTER	CENTER	TRUE	15



// end of custom properties

